Artists Space Archive

Contents

Series I: Exhibition Files

Dates:
1973 - 2009

Scope and Content

This series consists of materials generated by the production of exhibitions and events at Artists Space from 1973-2009. Comprising the bulk of the collection, this material includes notes, correspondence, budgets, artists' CVs and slides, press releases, loan forms, exhibition inventories, architectural plans, travel itineraries, press packets, announcement cards, brochures, press clippings, and research materials related to the exhibitions at Artists Space. There is also extensive documentation of many of the exhibitions and events, through correspondence and exhibition images. Particular strengths include material related to the controversial Witnesses: Against our Vanishing exhibition, the national tour of Putt Modernism, the Artists Select series, the AIDS forum, and many more.

Arrangement

The original order of this series has been retained, which is chronological by the opening date of the exhibition, where known. For a full list of the exhibition history of the gallery, please see: http://artistsspace.org/archive

31142054885192box: 94, folder: 9 (Material Type: Mixed Materials)

Series II: Promotional Materials

Dates:
1986 - 1992

Scope and Content

This series consists of a sampling of Artists Space newspapers, sent out as exhibition announcements, as well as a small number of production materials for these newspapers, documenting the process of their creation. In addition, there is a sampling of postcards and brochures, most of which come from the Film Series program, and span the years from 1986 to 1992. The brochures and postcards are duplicated in Series I: Exhibition Files.

Arrangement

These files arrived without an arrangement scheme, and were arranged chronologically by the archivist by the opening date of each exhibition, if known. The files are alphabetical within each year.

31142054885218box: 96, folder: 25 (Material Type: Mixed Materials)

Series III: Administrative Files

Dates:
1973 - 2007

Scope and Content

This series consists of materials generated by the day-to-day work of Artists Space. The material includes forms, templates, mailing lists, materials related to the administration of travel, materials for mailings, "workshops" files, correspondence, notes, forms, clippings, miscellany, meetings minutes, and staff retreat materials. This series contains two subseries, Gallery Organizationl and Workshops. Subseries B: Workshops contains materials generated by the production of a workshop series that Artists Space initiated in the first decade of the 2000s.

Arrangement

These files retain their original order and are arranged chronologically by year, but the archivist arranged the files alphabetically within year. This series has been divided into two series, A: Gallery Organization and B: Workshops, which document a series of public workshops that Artists Space conducted in the early 2000s.

31142054885317box: 106, folder: 7 (Material Type: Mixed Materials)

Series IV: Book Files

Dates:
1988 - 1998

Scope and Content

These materials are arranged alphabetically, then chronologically. This series includes documentation generated by the research, fundraising, and production of the never-produced 15th anniversary book, intended to be published in 1988. In addition, this series preserves materials generated by the production of the 25th anniversary book published in 1998, 5000 Artists Return to Artists Space: 25 Years. This book is available at Fales. It is clear that the 25th anniversary book relied heavily on research materials originally generated by the production of the 15th anniversary book. The materials in this series include drafts, budgets, correspondence, notes, images, funding sources, brochures, catalogs, slides, interview typescripts, chronology, notes, and other research materials.

31142054896025box: 122, folder: 3 (Material Type: Mixed Materials)

Series V: Independent Project Grants

Dates:
1979 - 20051998-2005

Scope and Content

This series consists of materials generated by the Independent Project Grant program administered by Artists Space. These grants were provided to artists to stage exhibitions, either solo or in groups. These were available to unrepresented New York artists to put on shows in non-commercial spaces in the New York area. The material consists of grant proposals, work samples, correspondence, and documentation of grant spending, budgeting and planning.

Arrangement

This series is arranged chronologically, and alphabetically within each year.

Independent Exhibitions Program, Emergency Materials Fund, Independent Project Grants Program (IPG)

Series VI: Curator Files

Dates:
1979 - 2007

Scope and Content

This series includes the administrative files of both Lauri Firstenberg and Christian Rattemeyer relating to exhibitions that they curated. The material Includes slides, cvs, correspondence, and other files related to exhibition planning.

Arrangement

The archivist followed the chronological arrangement for this series, and arranged the files alphabetically within years for clarity. The files were removed from their original binders for preservation purposes, and the folder titles note this.
